subSubSection.paragraph:
Ovipositor
(
Figs 93–95
). Tergite 10 shiny, brownish yellow. Cercus brownish yellow, slender, slightly longer than tergite 10, with tip narrowed and curved dorsally, outer margin with indistinct serration (
Fig. 93
). Hypovalva in shape of pale yellow, elongated and slender filament, with short trichia at tip (
Fig. 94
). Median incision between hypovalvae deeper than posterior margin of sternite 8. Lateral incision relatively deep and narrow (about twice as deep as maximal width). Lateral angle of sternite 8 obtusely rounded. Sternite 9 with anterior part lightly broadened, posterior part short (
Fig. 95
). Furca anteriorly narrowed, posteriorly broad. Bursa copulatrix with spermathecal ducts sclerotised at base, in shape of lightly curved dark brown process. Wall of bursa copulatrix on connection site with spermathecal ducts partially sclerotised, sclerotisation extended short distance along wall. Cul-de-sac of bursa copulatrix curved. Spermatheca nearly pear-shaped, distinctly broadened at base (
Fig. 27
).
